kaggle_ingest.py

The script cleans Kaggle’s Google Play Store dataset → fixes messy text → converts to numeric → removes duplicates → saves clean file.
| Library                 | Why Used                                                                        | Where Used                                                                       |
| ----------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `pandas` (`pd`)         | For loading, cleaning, and transforming tabular data (DataFrame operations).    | Throughout (`read_csv`, column renames, applying functions, saving cleaned CSV). |
| `numpy` (`np`)          | For representing missing values as `np.nan` and performing numeric ops.         | Used in parsing functions (`parse_installs`, `parse_size`).                      |
| `re`                    | For **regular expressions**, removing non-numeric characters (e.g., “10,000+”). | In all parsing functions to clean text before converting to numbers.             |
| `Path` (from `pathlib`) | For OS-independent folder creation and file handling.                           | Used in `main()` to ensure `outputs/` folder exists.                             |

1)->parse_installs(x)
👉 Converts values like "10,000+" → 10000
🧹 Removes symbols (+, ,), keeps digits only.

2️⃣ parse_price(x)
👉 Converts "$4.99", "₹120", "Free" → numeric float
💰 Replaces symbols, handles “Free” as 0.0.

3️⃣ parse_size(x)
👉 Converts "12M", "512k", "1.2G" → bytes
📦 Handles "Varies with device" as missing (NaN).

4)->standardize(df)
| Step           | Action                                              |
| -------------- | --------------------------------------------------- |
| Rename columns | Converts inconsistent names to clean snake_case     |
| Parse columns  | Uses above functions for installs, price, size      |
| Convert date   | `last_updated` → datetime                           |
| Deduplicate    | Keeps unique (app_name, category) with most reviews |
| Normalize text | Trim spaces, lowercase category                     |

5)->main() (S)
Runs full process:
🗂 Create outputs/ folder
📥 Load CSV (pd.read_csv)
🧽 Clean (standardize())
💾 Save cleaned CSV (to_csv)
✅ Print “Saved: …”

In Simple Words

Read raw file
Clean & convert columns
Remove duplicates
Save final dataset

